// Module namespacing: `im "path" as m` aliases a module, and `m.fn(...)` calls into
// it. The module's own functions are renamed under the alias (m_fn), so they're
// isolated — two modules can define the same name without colliding, and the
// imported names don't leak unqualified.
im "lib/nsmod.ail" as geo
println(geo.rect(4, 5))
println(geo.tri(6, 4))
